<h2>Machaut: La Messe de Nostre Dame</h2>

<dl>
<dt>Machaut: La Messe de Nostre Dame</dt>
<dd>Clemencic Consort / Ensemble Nova / Polifonica Lucchese e
Capella Santa Cecilia - Ren&eacute; Clemencic<br>
<i>Arte Nova 85289</i><br>
<i>Arte Nova 271 982</i></dd>
</dl>

<h3>Contents:</h3>
<p><ol>
<h4>Minstrels and beggars play at the entrance of the church</h4>
<li>Machaut: Quant je suis mis (instrumental)</li>
<li>Li Roi de Navarre: Chancon d'amour (accompanied recitation)</li>
<li>Machaut: Dame a qui m'ottri (instrumental)</li>
<li>Anon., Burgundy: C'est Guignolot de St. Lazo (voice,
hurdy-gurdy)</li>
<li>Machaut: Dou mal (instrumental)</li>
<h4>Entry into the church</h4>
<li>Anon., Faenza: Kyrie (organ)</li>
<li>Anon., Freiburger Augustinerbrevier: Ave maris stella (soloist,
choir)</li>
<li>Anon: Ave gloriosa (glockenspiel)</li>
<h4>La Messe de Nostre Dame</h4>
<li><strong>Kyrie Eleison</strong></li>
<li><strong>Gloria in Excelsis</strong></li>
<li>Li Roi de Navarre: Du tres douz non a la virge Marie
(recitation)</li>
<li>Anon: Ave virgo regia (instrumental)</li>
<li><strong>Credo in unum Deum</strong></li>
<li>Anon: Ave Regina (glockenspiel)</li>
<li>Anon: Verbum bonum et suave (soloist, choir)</li>
<li>Machaut: Dame, vostre doulz viaire (voice, accompaniment)</li>
<li>Anon: Adesto (organ)</li>
<li><strong>Sanctus</strong></li>
<li>Anon., Faenza: Sangilio (organ)</li>
<li><strong>Agnus Dei</strong></li>
<li>Anon: Agniaus dous (instrumental)<br>
Anon: Ave maris (instrumental)</li>
<li>Anon., Limoges: Ave nobilis (glockenspiel)</li>
<li>Anon: Astra polorum (soloist, choir)</li>
<li><strong>Ite missa est</strong></li>
</ol></p>

<p>Performers: Colin Mason (bass, conductor of Ensemble Nova),
Egisto Matteucci (conductor of Polifonica Lucchese e Capella Santa
Cecilia), James Curry (tenor), Bernd Lambauer (tenor), Gerd Kunda
(bass), Ren&eacute; Zosso (voice, hurdy-gurdy), Ren&eacute; Clemencic
(organ, glockenspiel), Marco Ambrosini (nickelharpa), Andr&aacute;s
Kecsk&eacute;s (kobos, moorish guitar, lute), Frantisek Pok (buisine,
bagpipe, tromba marina, cornett), Khosro Soltani (shawm), Esmail
Vasseghi (hammered dulcimer, percussion), Wolfgang Reithofer
(percussion)</p>

<p>Playing time: 70'</p>

<p>Recording date: May 1999 (Lucca, live)</p>

<p><b>Excerpts:</b><br>
[1]-[2], [5], [9], [12], [21], [22], [24] <a href="rca60986.htm">RCA
&quot;Red Seals&quot; 82876 60986 2</a> [CDx4] Tr&eacute;sors -
Moyen-&Acirc;ge
</p>

<p>This recording features a wide array of sonorities, the objective
being to illustrate the variety of medieval life as it impinged
upon the central place of social gathering, the church.  The mass
sections themselves are performed by an unaccompanied ensemble of
vocal soloists, with organ incipits.</p>

<p>According to Florian Chevallot, &quot;the piece <i>Ave virgo
regia</i> is actually a rundellus called <i>Ecce mundi
gaudium</i>.&quot;</p>

<p>Another quality budget interpretation devoted to Machaut's
mass:</p>

